c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 31 of the Trademark Act of 1946, referred to in subsec. (c)(3)(B), is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":", Commerce and Trade."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3b80139-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2013—Subsec. (c)(3)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/274/s1/j/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–274, § 1(j)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “this title,” for “sections 41, 42, and 376,” and “a proportionate share of the administrative costs of the Office” for “a share of the administrative costs of the Office relating to patents”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/274/s1/j/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–274, § 1(j)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a proportionate share of the administrative costs of the Office” for “a share of the administrative costs of the Office relating to trademarks”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as par. (1), substituted “shall, subject to paragraph (3), be available” for “shall be available”, struck out at end “All fees available to the Director under section 31 of the Trademark Act of 1946 shall be used only for the processing of trademark registrations and for other activities, services, and materials relating to trademarks and to cover a proportionate share of the administrative costs of the Patent and Trademark Office.”, and added pars. (2) and (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsecs. (a), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":" made technical correction to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":". See 1999 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsecs. (a), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Director” for “Commissioner”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Director” for “Commissioner” wherever appearing and, in second sentence, substituted “All fees available” for “Fees available” and “shall be used” for “may be used”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Director” for “Commissioner”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/358"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–358","children":[],"tail":" substituted first sentence for former first sentence which read as follows: “Revenues from fees shall be available to the Commissioner to carry out, to the extent provided in appropriation Acts, the activities of the Patent and Trademark Office.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/204/s5/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–204, § 5(e)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (c) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (c) read as follows: “Revenues from fees will be available to the Commissioner of Patents to carry out, to the extent provided for in appropriation Acts, the activities of the Patent and Trademark Office. Fees available to the Commissioner under section 31 of the Trademark Act of 1946, as amended ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1113"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 1113","children":[],"tail":"), shall be used exclusively for the processing of trademark registrations and for other services and materials related to trademarks.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/204/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–204, § 4","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":" struck out “, the provisions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s725e"},"text":"section 725e of title 31","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, notwithstanding” after “United States”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/247"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–247","children":[],"tail":" inserted provision that fees available to the Commissioner under section 31 of the Trademark Act of 1946, as amended ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1113"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 1113","children":[],"tail":"), be used exclusively for the processing of trademark registrations and for other services and materials related to trademarks."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/517"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–517","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provision relating to payment of patent fees as subsec. (a) and struck out provision that, except as provided in sections 361(b) and 376(b) of this title, the Commissioner deposit fees paid in the Treasury of the United States in such manner as directed by the Secretary of the Treasury, designated existing provision relating to return of excess amounts paid as subsec. (d), and added subsecs. (b) and (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/131"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–131","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, except as provided in sections 361(b) and 376(b) of this title,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf3b8013a-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3b8013b-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2013 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/274"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–274","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to proceedings commenced on or after such date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/274/s1/n"},"text":"section 1(n) of Pub. L. 112–274","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s5"},"text":"section 5 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3b8013c-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2011 Amendment",